30/11/2005
BRUSSELS, Belgium -- During a meeting Tuesday (29 November) with UNMIK chief Soren Jessen-Petersen, EU Enlargement Commissioner Olli Rehn reiterated that Kosovo must have a clear European perspective, regardless of the outcome of status negotiations. According to his spokesperson, Rehn also stressed that the ultimate goal in Kosovo must be the establishment of a multiethnic society. In a separate meeting, EU security chief Javier Solana reviewed the situation in the province with Martti Ahtisaari, the UN special envoy for Kosovo status negotiations.
In other news, Mamberto Giorgio, head of the EU office in Pristina, announced that the European Agency for Reconstruction would finance a census for Kosovo, expected in April. The last one was in 1991. (RTS, B92, Tanjug, Beta - 29/11/05)
